  "prompt": "What are some good old songs?",
  "response": "There are countless timeless classics that have stood the test of time and continue to be loved by generations. Here\u2019s a list of some iconic old songs across various genres and eras to consider:\n\n### **1950s-1960s**\n1. **Elvis Presley** - \"Can't Help Falling in Love\" (1961)\n2. **The Beatles** - \"Hey Jude\" (1968)\n3. **Chuck Berry** - \"Johnny B. Goode\" (1958)\n4. **Frank Sinatra** - \"Fly Me to the Moon\" (1964)\n5. **The Beach Boys** - \"God Only Knows\" (1966)\n6. **The Righteous Brothers** - \"Unchained Melody\" (1965)\n7. **Sam Cooke** - \"A Change Is Gonna Come\" (1964)\n8. **Ray Charles** - \"Georgia on My Mind\" (1960)\n9. **The Rolling Stones** - \"(I Can't Get No) Satisfaction\" (1965)\n10. **Aretha Franklin** - \"Respect\" (1967)\n\n### **1970s**\n1. **Queen** - \"Bohemian Rhapsody\" (1975)\n2. **Fleetwood Mac** - \"Go Your Own Way\" (1977)\n3. **Led Zeppelin** - \"Stairway to Heaven\" (1971)\n4. **Eagles** - \"Hotel California\" (1976)\n5. **Don McLean** - \"American Pie\" (1971)\n6. **ABBA** - \"Dancing Queen\" (1976)\n7. **Stevie Wonder** - \"Superstition\" (1972)\n8. **Pink Floyd** - \"Wish You Were Here\" (1975)\n9. **Marvin Gaye** - \"What's Going On\" (1971)\n10. **David Bowie** - \"Heroes\" (1977)\n\n### **1980s**\n1. **Michael Jackson** - \"Thriller\" (1982)\n2. **Prince** - \"Purple Rain\" (1984)\n3. **Whitney Houston** - \"I Wanna Dance with Somebody\" (1987)\n4. **Bon Jovi** - \"Livin' on a Prayer\" (1986)\n5. **The Cure** - \"Just Like Heaven\" (1987)\n6. **Tears for Fears** - \"Everybody Wants to Rule the World\" (1985)\n7. **Journey** - \"Don't Stop Believin'\" (1981)\n8. **Cyndi Lauper** - \"Time After Time\" (1983)\n9. **U2** - \"With or Without You\" (1987)\n10. **George Michael** - \"Careless Whisper\" (1984)\n\n### **1990s**\n1. **Nirvana** - \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" (1991)\n2. **Oasis** - \"Wonderwall\" (1995)\n3. **Mariah Carey** - \"Hero\" (1993)\n4. **Alanis Morissette** - \"You Oughta Know\" (1995)\n5. **TLC** - \"Waterfalls\" (1995)\n6. **Radiohead** - \"Creep\" (1992)\n7. **Backstreet Boys** - \"I Want It That Way\" (1999)\n8. **Red Hot Chili Peppers** - \"Under the Bridge\" (1991)\n9. **Ace of Base** - \"The Sign\" (1993)\n10. **Shania Twain** - \"You're Still the One\" (1998)\n\nThese songs span a variety of styles and moods, so there\u2019s something for everyone. Let me know if you\u2019d like recommendations for a specific genre or artist!",
